data.fullLabel:
T3DB:
Rotenone works by
interfering with the electron
transport chain in mitochondria.
Specifically, it inhibits
the transfer of electrons
from iron-sulfur centers
in complex I to ubiquinone.
This prevents NADH from being
converted into usable cellular
energy (ATP).
data.value: Rotenone works by interfering with the electron transport chain in mitochondria. Specifically, it inhibits the transfer of electrons from iron-sulfur centers in complex I to ubiquinone. This prevents NADH from being converted into usable cellular energy (ATP).
